=== Simple Lebensohl after double of their 2-level overcall

Simple means that we just use Lebensohl to distinguish between extras
and no-extras when forced to bid at the three-level.

Applies when: +
@ 2-level overcall was a #jump or non-jump#
@ double was in direct or balancing seat

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
|  1H   | (2D) | X  | (P)
|  ?    |      |    |
|  2H   |      |    | default bid
|  2S   |      |    | {S}-fit, min
| !2NT! |      |    | #Lebensohl#
|  3C   |      |    | nat., extras
|  3D   |      |    | nat., extras
|===

It is particularly important opposite a balancing double of
a two level overcall.

